#. <section class="sutta" id="sn7.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn7.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 7"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 7"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn7.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Arahantavagga"
msgstr "1. The Perfected Ones"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn7.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Dhanañjānīsutta"
msgstr "1. With Dhanañjānī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.160"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.344"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn7.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn7.1:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa dhanañjānī "
"nāma brāhmaṇī abhippasannā hoti buddhe ca dhamme ca saṅghe ca."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time a certain brahmin lady of the Bhāradvāja clan named "
"Dhanañjānī was devoted to the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn7.1:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dhanañjānī brāhmaṇī bhāradvājagottassa brāhmaṇassa bhattaṃ "
"upasaṃharantī upakkhalitvā tikkhattuṃ udānaṃ udānesi:"
msgstr ""
"Once, while she was bringing her husband his meal she tripped and spoke "
"these words of inspiration three times:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:2.1"
msgid "“Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"“Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:3.1"
msgid "Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:4.1"
msgid "Namo tassa bhagavato arahato sammāsambuddhassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Homage to that Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.345"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:5.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo dhanañjāniṃ brāhmaṇiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When she said this, the brahmin said to Dhanañjānī:"

msgctxt "sn7.1:5.2"
msgid ""
"“evamevaṃ panāyaṃ vasalī yasmiṃ vā tasmiṃ vā tassa muṇḍakassa samaṇassa "
"vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"“That’d be right. For the slightest thing this wretched lady spouts out "
"praise for that bald ascetic."

msgctxt "sn7.1:5.3"
msgid "Idāni tyāhaṃ, vasali, tassa satthuno vādaṃ āropessāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Right now, wretched woman, I’m going to refute your teacher’s doctrine!”"

msgctxt "sn7.1:5.4"
msgid ""
"“Na khvāhaṃ taṃ, brāhmaṇa, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake "
"sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya, yo tassa bhagavato vādaṃ "
"āropeyya arahato sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, I don’t see anyone in this world—with its gods, Māras, and "
"Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans—"
"who can refute the doctrine of the Blessed One, the perfected one, the fully "
"awakened Buddha."

#. VAR: gantvā vijānissasī”ti → gantvāpi jānissasīti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn7.1:5.5"
msgid "Api ca tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, gaccha, gantvā vijānissasī”ti."
msgstr "But anyway, you should go. When you’ve gone you’ll understand.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.161"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo kupito anattamano yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then the brahmin of the Bhāradvāja clan, angry and upset, went to the Buddha "
"and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn7.1:6.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "sn7.1:6.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ gāthāya "
"ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "and addressed the Buddha in verse:"

# reading jhatva in line with SN 1.71, see BB’s note there.
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:7.1"
msgid "“Kiṃsu chetvā sukhaṃ seti,"
msgstr "“When what is incinerated do you sleep at ease?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:7.2"
msgid "kiṃsu chetvā na socati;"
msgstr "When what is incinerated is there no sorrow?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:7.3"
msgid "Kissassu ekadhammassa,"
msgstr "What is the one thing"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:7.4"
msgid "vadhaṃ rocesi gotamā”ti."
msgstr "whose killing you approve?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.346"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:8.1"
msgid "“Kodhaṃ chetvā sukhaṃ seti,"
msgstr "“When anger’s incinerated you sleep at ease."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:8.2"
msgid "kodhaṃ chetvā na socati;"
msgstr "When anger’s incinerated there is no sorrow."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:8.3"
msgid "Kodhassa visamūlassa,"
msgstr "O brahmin, anger has a poisoned root"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:8.4"
msgid "madhuraggassa brāhmaṇa;"
msgstr "and a honey tip."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:8.5"
msgid "Vadhaṃ ariyā pasaṃsanti,"
msgstr "The noble ones praise its killing,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn7.1:8.6"
msgid "tañhi chetvā na socatī”ti."
msgstr "for when it’s incinerated there is no sorrow.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:9.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, the brahmin said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn7.1:9.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "sn7.1:9.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "sn7.1:9.4"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca "
"bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn7.1:9.5"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.347"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn7.1:10.1"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho bhāradvājagotto brāhmaṇo bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the brahmin received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s "
"presence."

msgctxt "sn7.1:10.2"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā bhāradvājo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī "
"pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Not long after his ordination, Venerable Bhāradvāja, living alone, "
"withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of "
"the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own "
"insight the goal for which people from good families rightly go forth from "
"the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "sn7.1:10.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "sn7.1:10.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Bhāradvāja became one of the perfected."
